Loitering has been defined as "being in the same place, under conditions that give a reasonable person reason to believe that the purpose of this behavior is to establish control of a certain territory by a street gang, scare others from this territory, or cover up illegal activities." In Portland , Oregon, there were large-scale campaigns against loitering and related violations [2]. Brazil
In Brazil, loitering is a crime in itself. In Article 59 of the 1941 Criminal Code, loitering (vadiagem) is defined as â€œself-involvement, by way of habit, in an idle lifestyle of a person capable of working, or a person whose income is not enough to obtain livelihood, or of a person deriving income from illegal activities.